    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>If you want to <a href="https://github.com/dnschneid/crouton/wiki/Build-kernel-headers-and-install-Virtualbox-(x86)">install Virtualbox on a crouton chroot</a>, you need kernel headers so that Virtualbox can compile modules.</p>

<p>My Toshiba Chromebook 2 (CB30-B-104) came with a 3.10.18 kernel. Building the headers can be a bit of a pain, so I share them here.</p>

<p><a href="/files/linux-headers_image-3.10.18_3.10.18-10.00.Custom_amd64.deb.zip">linux-headers_image-3.10.18_3.10.18-10.00.Custom_amd64.deb.zip</a></p>
